Prompt: prompts\improve1.txt 
-------------------------------------------- 
Rotation matrix is mathematically verified:
- Level flight: nose → [0,-1,0] ✓, right wing → [1,0,0] ✓, up → [0,0,1] ✓
- Pitch up 30°: nose gains +Z = 0.5 ✓
- Roll right 30°: right wing dips -Z = -0.5 ✓ (right bank = right wing down)

Here's a summary of all changes made:

---

**`aircraft.py`** (physics)
- Actuator lag: 0.95×prev + 0.05×cmd per step (was 0.9×prev + 0.1×cmd) — much heavier lag
- Added per-surface rate limiting (±0.6/s max)
- ELEV_GAIN: 0.8→0.45, AIL_GAIN: 1.5→0.8, RUDD_GAIN: 0.4→0.20 — authority reduction
- PITCH_DAMP: 4→7, ROLL_DAMP: 5→9, YAW_DAMP: 3→5 — damping increase
- PITCH_STAB: 1.5→2.5, ROLL_STAB: 3.5→5.5 — stronger static stability
- STALL_ALPHA: 14°→13°, STALL_NOSE_DOWN: 4→7, stall drag: 0.8→1.2× — better stall model
- Sideslip keel damping: 0.2→0.5 — improved coordinated turns

**`render/pygame_renderer.py`** (renderer)
- **Body frame corrected**: X=forward(nose), Y=right wing, Z=up (was X=right, Y=aft)
- **Rotation matrix rewritten** to match new frame — verified algebraically
- Debug axes enabled: red=X(fwd), green=Y(right), blue=Z(up)
- Camera SMOOTH: 0.05→0.04, chase offset moved further back (55→70 m)
- VIS_SMOOTH: 0.15→0.12 for smoother attitude interpolation

**`envs/fixed_wing_env.py`** (environment)
- Stall crash now requires 15 sustained stall steps (1.5 s) instead of instant crash
- action_smooth_weight default: 0.03→0.06
- Added surface saturation penalty (>85% deflection)
- Added angular rate penalty (discourages oscillation)
- Stall per-step penalty: -5.0→-3.0 (less harsh now that crash is delayed)

**`sim/curriculum.py`** (curriculum)
- Stabilize stage 1: roll_perturb 0.25→0.12 rad (±7°), pitch_perturb 0.12→0.06 rad (±3°), spd_range 9-12→10-12 m/s
- Cruise stage 2: roll_perturb 0.5→0.35, pitch_perturb 0.3→0.20 — gentler progression
